&gt; Copies an array from the specified source array, beginning at the specified position, to the specified position of the destination array.A subsequence of array components are copied from the source array referenced by src to the destination array referenced by dest. The number of components copied is equal to the length argument. The components at positions srcPos through srcPos+length-1 in the source array are copied into positions destPos through destPos+length-1, respectively, of the destination array.

means it copies consecutive elements from the source array, starting at srcPos, and puts them in the order they&#39;re in, in the destination array, starting from destPos.

